# Postfix Transport Maps for SMTPy Integration
# This file routes specific email addresses to the SMTPy SMTP receiver
#
# Format: pattern transport:nexthop
#
# Examples:
#   # Route all mail for a specific address to SMTPy
#   alias@atomdev.fr         smtp:[smtpy-smtp-receiver]:2525
#
#   # Route all mail for a subdomain to SMTPy
#   .aliases.atomdev.fr      smtp:[smtpy-smtp-receiver]:2525
#
#   # Route specific addresses to SMTPy
#   test@atomdev.fr          smtp:[smtpy-smtp-receiver]:2525
#   demo@atomdev.fr          smtp:[smtpy-smtp-receiver]:2525
#
# After editing, run:
#   docker exec mailserver bash -c "cp /tmp/docker-mailserver/postfix-transport /etc/postfix/transport && postmap /etc/postfix/transport && postfix reload"
#   Or simply restart the container: docker restart mailserver
#
# Documentation: http://www.postfix.org/transport.5.html

# SMTPy-managed aliases
# Add your alias addresses here to route them to SMTPy for processing
# Format: email_address smtp:[smtpy-smtp-receiver]:2525
#
# Example:
# myalias@atomdev.fr       smtp:[smtpy-smtp-receiver]:2525
